<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.157890>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Anisopechys crinitus. Non­ovigerous female A, dorsal; B, pleon, lateral view; C, pleotelson; D, antennule; E, antenna; F – G, labrum, lateral and dorsal views; H, mandible; J, maxillule endite, distal; K, cheliped. Scale bar 1 mm (A)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/157890/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.157877>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Anarthrura simplex. A, non­ovigerous female; B, pleon and pleotelson, lateral view; C, antennule; D, antenna; E, labrum and mandibles, ventral view; F, labrum, lateral view; G, mandible; H, maxillule endite, distal; J, right cheliped, with detail of anterior propodal seta; K, detail of fixed finger; L, maxilliped. Scale bar 1 mm (A), 0.55 mm (B), 0.37 mm (C – D, J), 0.28 mm (K – L), 0.14 mm (E – H)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/157877/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

